# midifileplayer: external clocking (manual "Speed and Clocking"): each clock
# on the `clock` input plays one 16th note of content (div 96 -> 24 file ticks
# per clock); the file's own tempo and `speed` are ignored.
# CHOSEN READING (the manual says clocks are internally multiplied for full
# resolution but gives no algorithm): clock edge n snaps the position to
# (n-1)*24 ticks (firing everything due), then advances smoothly toward n*24
# at the rate implied by the measured edge period, never crossing the next
# boundary early. So the tick-0 note-on fires on edge 1 and the noteoff at
# tick 96 = boundary 4 fires exactly on edge 5.
# Edges every 600 engine ticks: 0, 600, 1200, 1800, 2400 -> gate falls @2400.
midifile 1 4D546864000000060000000100604D54726B0000000C00903C6460803C0000FF2F00
patch <<<
[midifileplayer]
    loop = 0
    clock = I1
    gate = O1
>>>
@0 set I1 1
@0 expect O1 1
@100 set I1 0
@600 set I1 1
@700 set I1 0
@1200 set I1 1
@1300 set I1 0
@1800 set I1 1
@1900 set I1 0
@2390 expect O1 1
@2400 set I1 1
@2400 expect O1 0
